Very fair, apologies about the ambiguous communication 😅. In general I
meant 'we the Chromium community, who were/are happy to ship WebAuthn with
a similar tracking risk'. I am sure that the community consists of people
who are both more and less ok with that risk, and also acknowledge that
just because we've done it before doesn't *automatically* mean it's fine
here.

