We discussed this in the API owners meeting today (present: Chris, Yoav,
Vlad, Jeffrey, Daniel, Alex, me) and think it makes sense to ship matching
the initial value that Safari already shipped. At that point we expect
&lt;a  rel="nofollow" href="https://github.com/w3c/csswg-drafts/issues/12386"&gt;https://github.com/w3c/csswg-drafts/issues/12386&lt;/a&gt; to be resolved to match
the shipping implementations. In other words, this will be an opt-in.&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;pre&gt;

